# Trigger ownership and recursion protection

For each transition, designate exactly one component as responsible for invoking the next sequence action.

Valid strategies include:

```text
activity handler updates Contact and directly invokes router
```

or:

```text
activity handler updates Contact with workflow trigger enabled
Contact workflow invokes router
```

Do not use both for the same transition unless idempotency has been explicitly tested.

The Phase 1 report must state for every workflow:

```text
triggering module
triggering fields
function invoked
whether the update requests workflow execution
whether the function directly invokes another function
duplicate-execution risk
```

Unrelated Contact edits must not restart or advance a sequence.

Contact workflows must use specific field-change criteria rather than triggering sequence routing on every Contact edit.

