# Primary Contact assignment

Use `Deal.Contact_Name` as the sole Primary Contact lookup.

Apply these rules:

```text
New canonical Deal with no Primary Contact
→ assign the first valid converted Contact

Existing Deal with Contact_Name populated
→ do not replace it automatically when another Contact is linked

Existing Deal with Contact_Name blank
→ assign a valid linked Contact

Primary Contact replacement
→ explicit user action unless an existing approved workflow defines otherwise
```

When `Contact_Name` changes:

```text
sync Deal.Opportunity_Stage from the new Primary Contact.Stage
sync Deal.Opportunity_State from the new Primary Contact.State
sync Deal.Opportunity_Status from the new Primary Contact.Status
derive Deal.Stage from Deal.Opportunity_Stage
```

If the Primary Contact becomes Lost or Stopped:

```text
do not automatically mark the Deal Lost
do not automatically promote another Contact
identify whether another viable Contact exists
create or reuse an existing manual-review mechanism where supported
otherwise report the unresolved decision
```

Do not add a new Task Type or picklist value to support this without approval.

